reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 30, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Stopped working after 2 minutes! Save your time and money. Junk.
reviews.reviewText: I would not be as put off by the cheap plastic build quality if the lamp actually worked. My 3 YO daughter was excited to have the easy-on touch switch, which is also easy to locate in the dark because it has a tiny LED. However, the lamp quit after being on for two minutes and 2-3 on-off cycles of her learning the switch. I've tried other USB power adapters to no avail. Also, the clamp mount has no rubber or other material to keep it in place. It easily slides off of smooth/painted surfaces even when really tightened down. The base appears to be filled with cinder block or cement. I put it on a teak desk and coarse gray dust fell out and scratched the surface when I moved the base. This lamp set is total junk. I wouldn't bother with the return except for $20, it's really not acceptable. The manufacturer has serious quality assurance issues and needs to know it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 26, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Not ideal but it works
reviews.reviewText: Why's it so hard to find a decent LED desk lamp nowdays? I'm resigned to the fact that they stop working after a year or so - continually adjusting the position of the lamp wears the internal wires down til they break I suspect? So I order several cheap ones to have a replacement handy. So many of them have the trendy touch-activated thing which I HATE. Light turns on and off/dims every time I brush it or change the position. Never again! So I have to ignore all the lamps with that. I love a switch right on the lamp but they now all have them on the cords.Anyway, this lamp is decent I guess. It doesn't match what the reviews here say though. It's got a replaceable bulb and a standard cord (not USB as many reviews here mention). Brightness is OK for the size - could be brighter though, especially since I've had even smaller lamps that were plenty bright. The supplied bulb has a slight yellowish tone which could be good for ambient lighting but not ideal for close desktop work. The switch is on the cord, not on the lamp. Bah!The base is very light compared to even smaller lamps but it seems perfectly stable. I don't expect to have issues with that. One last thing: the instructions say to "carefully" insert the lamp into the base. Ha! Nope. You have to really push and shove that sucker, but it will go in eventually.I'd say for 19 bucks go ahead and buy it if you don't see something better. I loved my previous Newhouse lamp: DLST01-B. Perfect small size, bright, switch on the lamp not the cord. But they don't sell it anymore. I should have bought five of them.

reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Good while it lasted
reviews.reviewText: I was initially very happy with this lamp, but about 1 week after purchase, it refuses to function properly. Now, when plugged in, it exists at a constant dim glow. Tapping the touchscreen power switch does nothing to turn it on or off, brighten it, or do anything other than make it flicker. It is now useless. I cannot recommend this product to anyone.
Me gustò su tamaño y calidad. Creo que durará muchos años dándome buen servicio .

Esta lámpara de escritorio vino a sustituir a mi vieja lámpara IKEA, por el precio esperaba una calidad decente, sin embargo superó mis expectativas, es una lámpara muy bonita, el armado se siente macizo, claro no como mi lámpara IKEA, pero hace su trabajo, lo que más me gustó es que mediante el conector USB la puedes alimentar directamente desde la PC sin necesidad de utilizar supresores o clavijas adicionales, el botón de encendido touch no me deja buen sabor de boca porque no siento ese feedback al encenderla o apagarla, la luz de led es muy blanca hubiera preferido un color más cálido.. En general es un buen artículo a un precio razonable y se mira bonita.

Tiene buen diseño es un producto fuerte que se ve de calidad, no es costosa y no consume mucha energia, se ajusta muy bien ya sea conla base o con la abrazadera. La lámpara es grande no es mediana, la base es grande y pesada.Solo hay dos cosas a considerar:1 no hay remplazo de led, osea que si se te descompone, funde, o no enciende, debes cambiar toda la lampara. Aun asi la garantia dice que puede durar muchos muchos años.2 hubiera sido genial incorporar el interruptor en la base es incomodo porque cuelga el cableEn general es una excelente lampara.

reviews.reviewerName: Kevin Martin Alarcon EspinozaKevin Martin Alarcon Espinoza
reviews.reviewText: Muy buen producto, se ve que es de buena calidad, la iluminación es perfecta, es luz fría y hace que pueda leer a gusto por las noches. El pedido tardó un poco a mi parecer, pero todo muy bien.

Llego a tiempo, la lámpara es muy bonita y de buena calidad, tiene dos formas de usarse, una es con un clip directo a tu escritorio y la otra es con una base redonda bastante resistente que viene incluida. Me encanto la volvería a comprar.
